      "text": [
        " يُخَلَّى عَنِ الْبَعِيرِ فِي الْحَرَمِ يَأْكُلُ مَا شَاءَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Hammad, from Hareyz, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘You can free the camel inside the Al-Harram to eat whatever it so desires to’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from Hammad from Hariz who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Camels can be left in al-Haram (the sacred area) to eat whatever it likes.’” "
        ]
      }
